directory: crates/ctx-context/src
domain: Implements the ctx-context binary: computes the ordered chain of context-node paths (rollup.ctx/intent.md ancestors plus a leaf .ctx) above any repo file or directory, serves their contents with soft-absent handling, and injects unseen portions of that chain into Claude Code sessions via a fail-open PostToolUse hook. External consumers get two entry points: the CLI (path mode, manual invocation) and hook mode (stdin JSON, automatic injection), both funneled through `cli::dispatch`.
edit_notes:
  - All filesystem/env access in serve, session, chain, and hook goes through the `Env` trait (env.rs), never std::fs directly, so tests can substitute fakes; StdEnv is the only real impl, rooted at an absolute repo base path.
  - Chain node ordering/kind (chain.rs) is a protocol depended on by serve.rs (rendering) and hook.rs (fresh-node filtering); changing node kinds, order, or leaf-path derivation requires updating both consumers.
  - Session dedup ledger (session.rs, keyed by ENV_SESSION_ID or hook event's session_id) is shared between CLI path mode and hook mode — the JSON state file format/location must stay consistent across both call sites, and hook.rs's "fresh nodes" logic depends on it.
  - Untrusted path strings must enter the system only through `RepoPath::parse` (repo_path.rs); `child`/`under` are unchecked and assume pre-trusted segments — serve.rs's `parse_target` is the CLI-facing gate.
  - Crate-wide lint bans println!/eprintln!/print!; main.rs and cli.rs route all output through injected writers instead.
children:
  - lib.rs: Declares the module tree and states the crate's read-only, hook-injecting purpose; no logic.
  - main.rs: Process shell — argv/stdin/exit-code plumbing around cli::dispatch; only place allowed to touch real process I/O outside StdEnv.
  - cli.rs: Argv parsing and mode dispatch (hook vs path), wiring session recording to path-mode output.
  - hook.rs: PostToolUse hook logic — event parsing, path resolution, fail-open fresh-context injection.
  - serve.rs: Turns a resolved chain into rendered, absence-tolerant text output; defines the CLI/hook display contract.
  - chain.rs: Computes chain structure/ordering (rollup/intent/leaf nodes) consumed by serve.rs and hook.rs.
  - session.rs: Per-session served-node ledger backing hook dedup and CLI `--hook`-equivalent tracking.
  - repo_path.rs: Validated repo-relative path type; sole gate for untrusted path strings.
  - env.rs: `Env` trait + `StdEnv`, the filesystem/env-var abstraction all above modules depend on.
  - error.rs: Shared `CtxError` taxonomy; no `Box<dyn Error>`/anyhow anywhere in the crate.
invariants:
  - Hook-mode code paths (hook.rs, and cli::dispatch's hook branch) never propagate errors that would block the agent — failures degrade to empty/marker output, not process failure.
  - Chain resolution never reads or exposes source file bytes — only rollup.ctx, intent.md, and leaf `.ctx` contents flow through serve/hook.
  - All cross-module errors are `CtxError` variants (error.rs); no module introduces its own error type or dyn-Error boxing.